full_content.content: Common reasons your LG washer has no power
The most common reasons your LG washer has no power are a malfunctioning electronic control board, faulty user interface or a broken motor.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
LG washers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a LG washer

A malfunctioning electronic control board can lead to various failures in a washer. This is because the board serves as the brain of the washer, controlling crucial components such as the water valve, drive motor, drain pump, and cycles. If the electronic control board fails, the washer may not power up or display the cycle status. Additionally, it might fail to fill, agitate, spin, or drain. In some cases, a shorted board may emit a burning smell.
How to replace the electronic control board in a washer

A faulty user interface control may become unresponsive and won’t allow you to change wash cycle settings or turn the washer on and off. In some failures, only one or two buttons or dials on the interface are affected, but in some cases the entire interface will be completely dead. Cycle status such as time remaining in the cycle won’t display properly on a defective user interface. Control keys or buttons on the user interface may also stick, causing the washer to exhibit inconsistent behavior, such as starting or stopping unexpectedly during a cycle. Error codes may also be present.
How to replace a washer user interface control

A broken washer motor will prevent the spin basket from rotating or agitating, and can also cause a variety of other issues that affect the washer’s ability to function properly. Signs that the motor is wearing out include unusual noises during operation, such as grinding or squealing sounds. The washer may also exhibit erratic spinning or agitation, with clothes not being properly rinsed or still soaking wet after the spin cycle. Additionally, a worn-out motor may lead to the washer not completing its cycles, stopping abruptly, or not starting at all. Burnt smells or overheating around the motor area can be indicative of internal problems. In some cases, visible damage to the motor itself may be apparent.
How to replace the motor in a washer
What to expect when you experience an LG washer no power issue
How is the no power problem fixed?

Correcting most no power problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, user interface control or motor. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.

When your LG washer is completely unresponsive, start by ruling out the obvious--is it unplugged? Did the circuit breaker trip?

To test whether the electrical outlet is the problem, plug a hair dryer or other electrical device into it. If the hair dryer doesn't work, the wiring in the outlet is the problem. Have an electrician repair the electrical outlet.

What to look out for with a washer no power diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your washer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.
LG Washer Power Button not Working

When your LG washer power button is not working, unplug the washer power cord and press the power button for 5 seconds to reset the electronic control board. Plug the washer back in and see if the power button starts working. Resetting the control board in this manner may fix the problem.

If resetting the control board didn’t fix the power button problem, check the washer electrical outlet for power. Check the house circuit breaker for the washer outlet and reset that breaker if you find it tripped. That may restore power to the washer so the power button works.

If a tripped breaker isn’t causing the problem, test the electrical outlet by plugging a small lamp or night light into the outlet. If the electrical outlet is dead, have an electrician fix the outlet.

If these basic troubleshooting steps don’t help your fix the problem with your LG washer power button not working, then a bad electronic control board, defective control panel or wiring failure could be preventing the power button from working. full_content.content: Why isn’t my LG washer turning on?
Possible causes include a tripped circuit breaker, a blown fuse, or a malfunctioning power cord or control board.
How can I troubleshoot my LG washer if it has no power?
Check the power supply, test the circuit breaker, and inspect the power cord and control board for any issues.
Could a blown fuse cause my LG washer to lose power?
Yes, a blown fuse can prevent the washer from turning on. If the fuse is faulty, it should be replaced.
What should I check first if my LG washer isn’t turning on?
First, check the power cord and ensure it's plugged in. Then, inspect the fuse and circuit breaker for any faults.

full_content.content: How Does a Mixing Valve Work?
Learn how a mixing valve works to control water temperature in a washer.
What is the drum of the washing machine?
The drum is the core part of the washer that holds your laundry and enables the cleaning process through rotation, agitation, and rinsing.
Hard water is water that contains high levels of dissolved minerals, particularly calcium and magnesium. It contrasts with soft water, which has lower concentrations of these minerals.
What is a Washing Machine Pedestal?
A washing machine pedestal is a platform that raises the washer off the ground, providing easier access to the appliances and often includes additional storage space such as drawers.

A washer tub is the interior part of a washing machine where clothes are placed for washing, typically made of stainless steel, plastic, or porcelain-coated metal, designed to hold water and withstand the agitation or spinning during the wash cycle.
